WEBVTT

00:04:29.121 --> 00:04:32.288
But you know, this is how
forest research in Canada goes.

00:04:32.329 --> 00:04:33.788
(Laughter)

00:04:33.788 --> 00:04:35.329
So I came back the next day,

00:04:35.371 --> 00:04:37.621
and mama grizzly and her cub were gone.

00:04:37.621 --> 00:04:39.663
So this time, we really got started,

00:04:39.663 --> 00:04:42.454
and I pulled on my white paper suit,

00:04:42.496 --> 00:04:44.329
I put on my respirator,

00:04:46.163 --> 00:04:47.371
and then

00:04:47.413 --> 00:04:49.663
I put the plastic bags over my trees.

00:04:51.079 --> 00:04:53.163
I got my giant syringes,

00:04:53.204 --> 00:04:54.871
and I injected the bags

00:04:54.871 --> 00:04:58.288
with my tracer isotope
carbon dioxide gases,

00:04:58.329 --> 00:04:59.538
first the birch.

00:04:59.538 --> 00:05:02.538
I injected carbon-14, the radioactive gas,